review_blob: Coffee coffee coffee. And more coffee. Its pretty good. Not thick enough and a light head....I need more head.
Nice brew. Really fruity with a hop taste. Bitter bite but very light. Will drink again.
Dude I love this brew. Wish I had it up in Michigan. Easy and smooth to drink. Wish it had a better head.
Dirty little brew. Nice smooth head and a deep rich color. Perfect brew. Will drink again
Dirty sassy brew. Lots of flavor lots of pine. Makes you want to ask Kris Kringal over to dinner to bang your grandma. Nice palate and nice head.
Nice crisp bite. Easy on the way down. Taste of bitter nuts and sweet caramel. Nice thick head.
Decent. Kinda tastes like other shorts brew. Tangy taste with a crisp clean bite. Not enough head
Smells like a fresh summers eve during winter. Boasts a hell of a bite with a crisp clean finish. Kinda like a woman in a binki.
Scent of shit and throw up with a hint of malt. Smooth with a lasting bite. Eh. Over rated
Overall hoppiness of brew goes down smoothly. Nice crisp head. Leaves a rough after taste. Perfect for a 7abv though.
beer_name: Sierra Nevada Beer Camp Hoppy Lager
